schemas.name: ThiruTrip
schemas.description: Data Schema represents the information of a trip status

schemas.name: ThiruDriverStatus
schemas.description:
Schema represents the data format that the driver apps should be sending periodically 
that represent the "state" of the driver.
schemas.content:
{
  "definitions": {},
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "http://example.com/root.json",
  "type": "object",
  "title": "The Root Schema",
  "required": [
    "driver_id",
    "first_name",
    "last_name",
    "email",
    "phone_number",
    "picture",
    "promo_code",
    "rating",
    "activation_status"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "driver_id": {
      "$id": "#/properties/driver_id",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Driver_id Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "8LvWuRAq2511gmr8EMkovekFNa2848lyMaQevIto-aXmnK9oKNRtfTxYLgPq9OSt8EzAu5pDB7XiaQIrcp-zXgOA5EyK4h00U6D1o7aZpXIQah--U77Eh7LEBiksj2rahB=="
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "first_name": {
      "$id": "#/properties/first_name",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The First_name Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "Uber"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "last_name": {
      "$id": "#/properties/last_name",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Last_name Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "Tester"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "email": {
      "$id": "#/properties/email",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Email Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "uber.developer+tester@example.com"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "phone_number": {
      "$id": "#/properties/phone_number",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Phone_number Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "+14155550000"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "picture": {
      "$id": "#/properties/picture",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Picture Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "https://d1w2poirtb3as9.cloudfront.net/16ce502f4767f17b120e.png"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "promo_code": {
      "$id": "#/properties/promo_code",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Promo_code Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "ubert4544ue"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "rating": {
      "$id": "#/properties/rating",
      "type": "integer",
      "title": "The Rating Schema",
      "default": 0,
      "examples": [
        5
      ]
    },
    "activation_status": {
      "$id": "#/properties/activation_status",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Activation_status Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "active"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    }
  }
}

schemas.name: ThiruDriverRideAccept
schemas.description: Data format that represents the information required for a driver to accept a ride.

schemas.name: ThiruDriverPayment
schemas.description:
This Schema represents the data needed to inform drivers about being paid for a given ride 
and the payment breakdown

schemas.name: ThiruRideReceipt
schemas.description:
This Schema conforms to the format of a customer receipt and should only be used when 
providing receipts to end customers.
schemas.content:
{
  "definitions": {},
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "http://example.com/root.json",
  "type": "object",
  "title": "The Root Schema",
  "required": [
    "request_id",
    "subtotal",
    "total_charged",
    "total_owed",
    "total_fare",
    "currency_code",
    "charge_adjustments",
    "duration",
    "distance",
    "distance_label"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "request_id": {
      "$id": "#/properties/request_id",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Request_id Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "b5512127-a134-4bf4-b1ba-fe9f48f56d9d"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "subtotal": {
      "$id": "#/properties/subtotal",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Subtotal Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "$12.78"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "total_charged": {
      "$id": "#/properties/total_charged",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Total_charged Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "$5.92"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "total_owed": {
      "$id": "#/properties/total_owed",
      "type": "null",
      "title": "The Total_owed Schema",
      "default": null,
      "examples": [
        null
      ]
    },
    "total_fare": {
      "$id": "#/properties/total_fare",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Total_fare Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "$5.92"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "currency_code": {
      "$id": "#/properties/currency_code",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Currency_code Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "USD"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "charge_adjustments": {
      "$id": "#/properties/charge_adjustments",
      "type": "array",
      "title": "The Charge_adjustments Schema"
    },
    "duration": {
      "$id": "#/properties/duration",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Duration Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "00:11:35"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "distance": {
      "$id": "#/properties/distance",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Distance Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "1.49"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    },
    "distance_label": {
      "$id": "#/properties/distance_label",
      "type": "string",
      "title": "The Distance_label Schema",
      "default": "",
      "examples": [
        "miles"
      ],
      "pattern": "^(.*)$"
    }
  }
}

schemas.name: ThiruRideRequest

events.name: DriverStatusUpdated
events.description: When a driver status changes, this event is generated to notify up status changes.

events.name: ThiruDriverRideAccepted
events.description: This is the application that a driver uses to interact with the Acme Rideshare ecosystem

events.name: ThiruDriverRideRequested
events.description:
This is the event triggered to active drivers that are within a geospatial proximity to the 
passenger

events.name: ThiruRideRequest
events.description: This is the event that is fired when a customer has confirmed they want a ride.

events.name: ThiruRideAccepted
events.description:
This is the event which is fired when a ride has been accepted and committed to by a 
driver.

events.name: ThiruTripUpdated
events.description: This is the event which is fired periodically when a driver is on an active trip.

events.name: ThiruDriverFundsDeposited
events.description: This event is triggered after billing has successfully deposited money into a drivers account

events.name: ThiruCustomerReceiptGenerated
events.description:
This is the event which contains a customers receipt information once payment has gone 
though

applications.name: Thiru Passenger App
applications.description:
This is the app that a user of acme rideshare uses in order to obtain rides from willing 
drivers.

applications.name: Thiru Driver Management
applications.description:
This application controls which rides need to be fulfilled, which are in route, and 
completed

applications.name: Thiru Driver App
applications.description: This is the application that a driver uses to interact with the Acme Rideshare ecosystem.

applications.name: Thiru Billing App
applications.description: This app processes customer payments and also pays the drivers.
